commitResults.messageTitle: Logic: Modify AddProductCommmand to add product to model.
commitResults.messageBody:
main:
* Add methods hasProduct, addProduct and deleteProduct in Model;
  implement the first two in ModelManager.

* Add method getProductList in ReadOnlyAddressBook; implement it in
  MyCRM.

* Add method isSameProduct in Product that returns true if products
  have the same name.

* Modify ProductBuilder so that it can change fields of the product
  to build.

* Add class ProductNameContainsKeywordPredicate.

* Add class UniqueProductList which is a product list that keeps
  product unique by product names.

* Add DuplicateProductException and ProductNotFoundException to
  represents problematic operations when manipulating
  UniqueProductList.

* Add TypicalProducts that contains some products with all the
  fields being non-empty and provides a method that returns an
  MyCrm containing the typical products.

* Add an import in CommandException to make javadoc show correctly.

test:
* Add tests to test newly added methods in MyCRM and ModelManager.

* Implement methods in model stubs in AddContactCommandTest and
  AddTemplateCommandTest.

* Modify AddProductCommandTest so that it tests execute method.

* Add a test in ProductTest to test isSameProduct method.

* Add AddProductCommandIntegrationTest to test interaction
  between AddProductCommand and model.

* Add UniqueProductListTest to test unique list operations.

* Add ProductNameContainsKeywordPredicateTest.

commitResults.messageTitle: Ui: Add ProductListPanel in MainWindow to display products.
commitResults.messageBody:
main:
* Create ProductCard that holds info of a product. Add corresponding
  FXML file.

* Create ProductListPanel. Add corresponding FXML file.

* Add getFilteredProductList() to Logic; implement it in
  LogicManager.

* Modify handleTemplate() in Mainwindow to let it display product
  panel only.

test:
* Add a test in LogicManagerTest to test newly added method.

Note:
* To display contacts/templates, need to modify fillInnerParts()
  and handleTemplate() methods.

main:
* Add class DeleteProductCommandParser that takes in deleteProduct
  command and returns DeleteProductCommand object.

* Add MESSAGE_INVALID_PRODUCT_DISPLAYED_INDEX in Messages to
  indicate product index is invalid.

* Modify MyCrmParser to let it recognize command words of newly
  added commands.

* Implement ModleManager#deleteProduct().

* Add CommandTestUtil#showProductAtIndex() that takes in a model
 and a index and set filtered list to only show the product at given
 index.

* Add a typical product in TypicalProduct and ProductBuilder.

* Add product indexes in TypicalIndexes.

test:
* Add a test in MyCrmParserTest to test if MyCrmParser parse delete
  command correctly.

* Add tests for DeleteProductCommand, ListProductCommand and
  DeleteProductCommandParser.

commitResults.messageTitle: Logic: Add enum CommandType and assign it to each command.
commitResults.messageBody:
main:
* Add an abstract method Command#getType() that returns type of the
  command.

* Add COMMAND_TYPE and override getType() in each command.

* Add CommandType as a field of CommandResult.

NOTE: Now to construct a CommandType, you can pass message and
      command type as argument, or you can just pass the message and
      command type will be set to CommandType.COMMON by default.

* Modify MainWindow#executeCommand() that it shows panel that
  correspond to command type of command result.

* Set contact list panel as the first shown panel.

test:
* Adjust constructors of CommandResult in tests to pass in the
  correct arguments.
